courses.learning_outcomes:
Student should be able to:
- Appreciate inter-disciplinary approaches in health improvement;
- Understand how to design, implement and evaluate health improvement programs using common theoretical frameworks;
- Appreciate the role of community involvement, grass-roots organizations, advocacy groups and the role of government in health promotion;
- Become familiarized with real-life examples of health promotion successes and failures.

Student should be able to:
1. Understand key communication theories that explain how people process health communication messages;
2. Understand how to plan a health communication campaign;
3. Develop health messages based on audience research.
